-- Mobinil May Sign Deal on Network Infrastructure in Egypt, Al Mal Reports
-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 2010-09-27T05:17:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/mobinil-may-sign-deal-on-network-infrastructure-in-egypt-al-mal-reports.html
The Egyptian Co. for Mobile
Services, or Mobinil, may sign an agreement soon to build
telecommunications infrastructure for a road linking Upper Egypt
to the Red Sea , Al Mal  reported, citing a government official.  The road will have 30 communication points, each costing
between 2 million and 3 million Egyptian pounds ($351,000 to
$526,000), Al Mal said, citing Mohamed Hosni, the chairman of
the state-run Upper Egypt-Red Sea Investment and Development Co.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ola Galal at 
 ogalal@bloomberg.net . 